		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.502-4</ph> Multiple-award contracts and small business set-asides.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d1176e13" class="- topic/p ">In accordance with section 1331 of Public Law 111-240 (<ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref "> 15 U.S.C. 644(r)</xref>
				        </ph>) contracting officers may, at their discretion-</p>
			      <ol id="d1162e22" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1176e26" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            When conducting multiple-award procurements using full and open competition, reserve one or more contract awards for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                        base="i1101771"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3). The specific program eligibility requirements identified in this part apply;</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1176e38" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Set aside part or parts of a multiple-award contract for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                        base="i1101771"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3). The specific program eligibility requirements identified in this part apply; or</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1176e50" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Set aside orders placed under multiple-award contracts for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                        base="i1101771"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3). For orders placed under the Federal Supply Schedules Program see <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref>. For all other multiple-award contracts see <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                        base="i1104008"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
